# SIGIL - security-shallots
SIGIL_VERSION: 1
PROJECT: security-shallots
HOST: YOUR_SERVER_HOSTNAME (YOUR_SERVER_IP)
REPO: /path/to/security-shallots/
UPDATED: YYYY-MM-DD

## What this is
Self-hosted SIEM on YOUR_SERVER. Dashboard at https://YOUR_SERVER_IP:8844.

## Instant access
```
Dashboard:  https://YOUR_SERVER_IP:8844
Auth:       YOUR_USERNAME / YOUR_PASSWORD
API base:   curl -sk -u "YOUR_USERNAME:YOUR_PASSWORD" https://YOUR_SERVER_IP:8844
```

## Key commands
```bash
# Health
curl -sk -u "USER:PASS" https://YOUR_SERVER_IP:8844/api/health | python3 -m json.tool

# Check if running
ps aux | grep shallots | grep -v grep

# Tail logs
tail -f /tmp/shallotd.log

# Restart
pkill -f 'python.*shallots'
cd /path/to/security-shallots
nohup .venv/bin/python -m shallots -c config.yaml run > /tmp/shallotd.log 2>&1 &

# Deploy code change
rsync -av shallots/ user@YOUR_SERVER:/path/to/security-shallots/shallots/
# then restart as above

# Run tests
python3 -m pytest tests/ -q
```

## Network map
```
INTERNET → YOUR_INTERFACE ← Suricata watches this
                │
    ┌───────────┴───────────┐
YOUR_SERVER             OTHER_MACHINES
  SIEM / shallots.db      (agents, sensors)
```

